  
  Algorithm:
  ----------	
  Foreground Segmentation using Adaptive 3 Phase Background Model

  Requirements:
 --------------
  Linux OS and opencv 2.4.9  

  Steps:
  --------

1. Copy the object-code (3PBMCode.o) in your directory
2. Put a video file (.avi or .mp4 type) in the same directory
3. Open a terminal in the same directory 
   to run the object-code by typing

  ./3PBMCode.o video.avi 

   where
   video.avi   : input video file

A folder will be create in the current directory
named "3pbmRESULT" and all the binary images
will be load there.

Note: If you get a 'permission denied' error, change the 
permission of 3PBMCode.o by typing 

chmod 777 3PBMCode.o 

in the terminal (current directory).


